# Workflow: user wording does not shorten the merge bar

**Hard law:** if a user message conflicts with this, **`AGENTS.md`** and this rule win unless they **explicitly waive bot closeout in writing for that PR** (**`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**, Exceptions).

## Never waives **`AGENTS.md`** steps 5–7 or the gate below

- Throughput phrases: “merge everything”, “close all PRs”, “batch merge”, “land the queue”, etc.
- Urgency, frustration, “just merge.”
- “CI green” / “checks passed” while threads are missing, still loading in the PR UI, or unreplied.
- Skipping **~10–15 minutes** post–green-CI re-poll (**unless written waiver for that PR**).

## Merge / first-time auto-merge

Execute the full **Bot feedback wait gate** + threaded replies in **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**—do not restate those steps here (single source of truth).

## If pressured to merge without closure

Say merge is **forbidden** until gate + replies; offer **written waiver for that PR** or proceed with the gate.

## Pointers

- **`AGENTS.md`** — ship bar
